; M3 gate: velocity macros that drive the level to silence, then a new note.
; A :vel macro modulates the composed output (FM carrier TL / PSG attenuation),
; without corrupting the channel's keyed state — so when the macro reaches vel 0
; (att 15, silent) and the next note switches macros, the new note still keys and
; its envelope sounds. This is the noise-drum pattern from demo1; it caught the
; PSG "keyed vs audible" conflation (driver.md §13.3).
(noise :tempo 120 :len 8
  (macro :vel [15 8 2]) c c
  (macro :vel [15 12 9 6 3 0]) c c
  (macro :vel [11 0]) c c c)
(sqr1 :len 8 :vel 13
  (macro :vel [15 6 0]) c e
  (macro :vel [15 10 5 0]) g c)
(fm1 :alg 4 :fb 3 :ar1 31 :tl1 20 :ar4 31 :tl4 8 :len 8
  (macro :vel [15 8 0]) c e g c)
